{
  "texts": [
    "Since then, low-level computer languages, like assembly language, replaced punch cards.",
    "Later higher-level programming languages like Basic, C, Java, and Python replaced assembly language.",
    "The human-machine interface (HMI) also switched from in-line typing (e.g., disk operating system) to a graphical user's interface (GUI{XE \"GUI:graphical user's interface\"}) with application icons.",
    "At the time of this writing, humanity has entered a new era of HMI where users can use language to interact with computers more naturally.",
    "This capability has increased the accessibility of computers to a much larger population."
  ]
}